---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Nick Stambaugh - Referral Links">
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 sm:py-24 space-y-12">
    <header>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-secondary dark:text-dk-accent"
      >
        Referral Links
      </h1>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-6">
      <div
        class="border border-text/10 dark:border-dk-text/10 rounded-xl p-6 bg-secondary/5 dark:bg-dk-secondary/5"
      >
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text dark:text-dk-accent">
          Proton
        </h2>

        <p class="mt-3 text-text dark:text-dk-text leading-relaxed">
          I use Proton for a lot of my personal digital life: email, calendar,
          Drive storage, VPN, password management, aliases, and simple documents
          and spreadsheets.

          I wrote more about why I started using it in
          <a
            href="/posts/moving-more-of-my-digital-life-somewhere-less-creepy"
            class="text-secondary dark:text-dk-accent hover:underline underline-offset-4"
          >
            this post</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-text dark:text-dk-text leading-relaxed">
          If you decide to try Proton, using my referral link helps support
          this site:
        </p>

        <a
          href="https://pr.tn/ref/X0J3A3B2"
          class="inline-flex items-center mt-5 text-sm font-medium text-secondary dark:text-dk-accent hover:underline underline-offset-4"
        >
          Try Proton →
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <p class="text-sm text-text/60 dark:text-dk-text/60 leading-relaxed">
        I only include referral links for products or services I actually use.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>